What is React? 

React is a javascript library for building UI

React app run in the browser don't run on the server

React is a component

Props is outside of the component

State is inside of the component

Component LifeCycle

1. Only available in stateful components

2. constructor()

3. componentWillMount()

4. componentDidMount()

5. componentWillReceiveProps()

6. componentWillUpdate()

7. componentDidUpdate()

8. componentDidCatch()

9. shouldComponentUpdate()

10. componentWillUmount()

11. render()
React is composition Model
React Declarative nature
The Way data flow through a component
And the react is really just Javascript

What is the “Virtual DOM”?

The virtual DOM (VDOM) is a programming concept where an ideal, or “virtual”, representation of a UI is kept in memory and synced with the “real” DOM by a library such as ReactDOM. This process is called reconciliation. ... They may also be considered a part of “virtual DOM” implementation in React.
